<br>
We hear all the time about how the Warrior couldn't do his/her job.  And we all know what utter bunk that is, because for the most part the game is designed to make it as difficult as possible for us to do our job unless everyone cooperates.  Yet we still hear it.  Go over to Monkly business and you'll hear see Monk's pissing and moaning about how the group Warrior couldn't hold agro.  You'll here the same in the Safe House from the Rogues.  It gets old after a while.<br>
<br>
I recently joined a guild.  And at one of the raids I was SAing.  I was using a Wavecrasher primary hand and an ornate blade of the General off hand.  Neither of these are great, but neither are horrible either.  And eventually I got bumped from what I was doing for a Warrior who had a Willsapper and something else.  Mainly because I didn't have the 'snap' agro they wanted.   Can't say I blame them for wanting the best possible agro control.  But it sucks that its so difficult for the Warrriors.<br>
<br>
