<br>
As a ranger, I am crunchy enough in milk as it is thank you. I do not need to take even more damage than I already do when hit. My maxed out defensive stats are lower than all other melee and hybrid classes. When you add in the low hit points and low AC, I tank plenty of damage as it is and can drop very fast.<br>
<br>
Anyone who thinks that rangers need to take even more damage than they already do, truely does not understand the nature of the class. We are not so much tanks as a master of agro control. On one hand we have ways to gain agro quickly, while on the other we can ditch unwanted agro fast. While I can melee well, many a day I would rather just stand back and rain deadly arrows down on my foe. I have this taunt skill, but I really do not like having things beating me and trying to kill me. A ranger has enough problems as it is and is often times at odds with himself.<br>
<br>
Should you find a ranger tanking, it is usually because a more beefy tanking class wasn't around to do the job or the beefy tank was very poorly equipted. [Sorry, I believe that I should be able to out tank a warrior in crafted wielding Wurmslayer and some other sucky weapon with no haste.] I so rarely tank by choice. If I do, it is probably because I am soloing while LFG.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Now we no longer have the best gear, instead the same gear is shared by most if not all of the other classes. Warriors lost nothing directly here, however the other classes became as powerful as a warrior in this point.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Oddly enough, rangers tend to feel the same in terms of weapons and SOV...<br>
Other classes have gained offensive power, including the knights that should be weaker than us, while we have gained nothing in terms of offensive strength.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> The hybrid classes, sans bards, have received the full force of the caster balance without suffering any drawbacks to the melee side of their powers. The healing hybrid classes have also received part of the priest balance as to date.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The only balance that rangers received as a result of this is the removeal of the non-cleric healing penality. Our best healing spell only heals 300HP. That isn't going to make me either group healer or raid healer. Paladins benefit a lot from this change. All other caster balancing has had no noticable effect on my class either way.<br>
