<br>
If you would be so kind as to read most of Seventhswords posts, he very clearly supports warriors tanking better than paladins and Shadowknights, he just doesn't want the difference to be as much as most warriors here want it to be.<br>
<br>
Incidentally, let me share a hypothetical group with you.<br>
<br>
Shaman<br>
Paladin<br>
Rogue<br>
Rogue<br>
Monk<br>
Wizard<br>
<br>
Nice group at 60, right?  They do lots of damage (four DPS classes) and have a tank (paladin) and a healer (shaman) plus the Paladin can backup heal and/or downtime heal.<br>
<br>
What if the paladin were an inefficient tank?  By that I mean he ended up at 2bubbles of health at the end of every fight and the shaman was spending 2 bubbles of mana or more healing him, and he was constantly oom from healing himself?<br>
<br>
Well, then you would want a warrior, right?<br>
<br>
But then where would the paladin fit into a group?  He could do the healing role **IF** he invested a lot of AAXP into getting healing skills and if he had some good focus gear.  But if he was a tank oriented paladin (I call that a crusader), or if he wasn't level 60 and didn't have Celestial Cleansing? Even if he WAS 60 with good AA skills, he wouldn't have the buffs that the shaman could offer the group.<br>
<br>
The point a lot of paladins want all of you to understand (and it's NOT that we are weak anymore or underpowered) is that paladins have a lot of utility, yes.  BUT all that utility mimics some other classes abilities.  AND they can do it better than we can.<br>
<br>
If you drop a tank because he's inefficient, why would you want to get a healer/buffer who is inefficient?  You wouldn't, you'd take a shaman at level 56 over a level 60 paladin, IF the paladin couldn't tank efficiently.  In the end, there are only so many roles that can be filled in an xp group, and the only one that paladins can fit into well is the role of tank.  Not DPS, not healer.  If warriors become the recognizably best tanks around, paladins will end up without xp groups.  Again.<br>
<br>
While we desperately want to avoid that, high end paladins as a whole DO NOT want to see the paladin class get Defensive.  They recognize that this would effectively remove the need for warriors.  Many high-end paladins now recognize that there is an issue with warriors in xp groups at the high end, and are advocating changes to taunt OR to mitigation.<br>
<br>
Again, remember, Seventhsword has advocated and will support changes to mitigation to improve warriors, shadowknights and paladins.  He just wants to ensure that warriors are not so far ahead of shadowknights and paladins as to make the &quot;lesser&quot; two classes undesired in xp groups.  That has happened in the past, and paladins who were there at the time are passionate about seeing that it doesn't happen again.<br>
<br>
