Defensive and evasive are useless most of the time in groups.  No advantage there.  So, if you had a choice between a tank that would lose 1 bubble of health per mob and one that would lose 1 and a half bubbles of health per mob but could stun, heal, root, LoH, etc, who would you pick?<br>
<br>
Seriously, think about it.  The healing really isn't an issue. Either the Shamen or the Cleric is going to be able to keep up just fine under most experience scenarios given tanks of that calibre.  Either class can tank more than acceptably.  So why go with the Warrior?  The Paladin can even heal himself at the end of most battles and not even lose much time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usurlok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Surlok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/02 7:49:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1056.topic&index=60>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fixing the warriors in PoP and addressing taunt concerns</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> RoK boosted warriors taunt with both disc and new weapons<br>
